
[1]melanite

   MEL'ANITE, n. [Gr. black.] A mineral, a variety of garnet, of a velvet
   black or grayish black, occurring always in crystals of a dodecahedral
   form.

   Melanite is perfectly opake. It is found among volcanic substances.
